'''Torstein Dahle''' (born 20 February 1947) is a Norwegian politician and economist. He works at the [[Bergen University College]] and represents [[Red (Norway)|Red]] in the city council of [[Bergen]]. Dahle was born in [[Oslo]].

Since its foundation in 2007 Dahle was leader of the [[Red (Norway)|Red]], and he was previously leader of Red's predecessor, [[Red Electoral Alliance]]. He was succeeded by [[Turid Thomassen]] in 2010.  He was also a founding member of [[Red Electoral Alliance]] and [[Workers' Communist Party (Norway)|Workers' Communist Party]] in 1973, but left the latter in 1997.

On 23 July 2007 he became subject to media attention when he said that the [[Taliban]] and other Afghan rebels had the full right of fighting the Norwegian soldiers of the [[International Security Assistance Force]] force stationed in [[Afghanistan]].<ref>[http://www.vg.no/pub/vgart.hbs?artid=153500 Full rett til <U+00E5> kjempe mot NATO-soldater] {{no icon}}</ref> The attention occurred only days later with the death of that occurred when a [[Royal Norwegian Army|Norwegian army officer]] in the [[Logar Province]] as a Norwegian military unit came under hostile fire.<ref>[http://www.vg.no/pub/vgart.hbs?artid=153480 Styrkene m<U+00E5>tte skyte seg ut - Erfaren norsk offiser drept i Afghanistan], vg.no {{no icon}}</ref> He later commented that he did not support the death of Norwegian military personnel.

Dahle is 204 cm tall and openly homosexual.<ref>[http://www.dagogtid.no/arkiv/1997/35/dahle.html ''Dag og Tid'' article] {{no icon}}</ref>

